        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 4:40PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 440 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Gladewater, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Gladewater, Gilmer, Big Sandy, Hawkins, West Mountain, Winona,
Union Grove, Warren City, Pritchett and Red Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
